The Federal Government has appointed Mr. Sunday Thomas as the Acting Commissioner for Insurance and Chief Executive Officer of the National Insurance Commission (NAICOM). The directive came through via a statement signed by the Deputy Director, Home Finances, Mr. A. O. Bello, for the Permanent Secretary of the Ministry of Finance. “I am directed to refer to a letter referenced NAICOM/FMF/DCTO/002 dated 2nd August, 2019 on the above subject and convey the approval for Mr. Sunday Thomas, Deputy Commissioner (Technical) to oversee the affairs of the Commission, pending the appointment of a substantive Commissioner for Insurance by Mr. President,” the statement said. It added that the appointment “is to ensure the effective administration of the Commission in line with the provisions of the National Insurance Commission Act (1997).” Recall the four-year tenure expiration of Alhaji Mohammed Kari expired on July 30, as the Commissioner for Insurance and Chief Executive of NAICOM. Until his recent appointment, Thomas served the apex Insurance regulatory body as the Deputy Commissioner (Technical) during the tenure of Kari. He was appointed in April 2017 after a 17 years stint at the Commission, working in and heading the inspectorate unit. He was earlier appointed the Director-General, Nigerian Insurers Association (NIA) on May 1, 2010; this he did for seven years. Assets: NAICOM chiefs fail to appear before CCB ‘We are ready for insurance investors’ Buhari appoints new heads for 23 federal agencies Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin